<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-27-0335 </DOCNO><TEXT>This article describes the Spills Action Centre (SAC) with respect tohow it can be used to respond to spills and other urgent environmentalconcerns. SAC began operating on November 29, 1985 to help implementPart IX of the Environmental Protection Act. It has a twenty-four hourtoll-free number that can be used to report spills and a full-time staffthat can assess the environmental impact of a spill and ensure that thespill is cleaned up. The article outlines all of SAC's responsibilitiesand its plans for the future.</TEXT></DOC>